  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "1 Adult Serving = 2 Kids Servings\nCook the pasta following pack instructions. Reserve a mugful of pasta water before draining."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, zest and juice the lime. Peel and crush the garlic. Halve the avocados, remove the stones and scoop the flesh into a blender or food processor."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Grate the Parmesan and add it to the blender with the garlic, avocado, lime juice and zest, olive oil, a good pinch of salt and a splash of pasta water. Blitz until smooth and creamy, adding more water if needed to loosen.\nTaste and add extra lime juice, if you'd like it extra zingy."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the pasta is cooked and drained, return it to the pan and pour over the avocado sauce. Toss until everything is well coated."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve up!\nKids Plate: Dish up as is for the kiddies. \nParents Plate: Dish up the pasta with extra Parmesan, a crack of black pepper, basil leaves and a sprinkling of chilli flakes."
    }
  ],
  "tips": [
    "Use vegan Parmesan or nutritional yeast to make it vegan.",
    "Great hot or cold — works as a pasta salad too.",
    "Add toasted seeds or rocket on top for extra texture."
